<!-- Story Pages -->
<div class="story-page" id="adam">
  <h2>Prophet Adam (آدم)</h2>
  <img src="https://www.grunge.com/img/gallery/why-the-adam-and-eve-story-stirs-up-so-much-controversy/some-arent-convinced-they-knew-right-from-wrong-1662422971.jpg" alt="Garden" class="story-image">
  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Adam عليه السلام was the first human created by Allah from clay and the first Prophet. Allah taught him the names of all things and commanded the angels to prostrate before him. He lived with his wife Hawwa (Eve) in Paradise until they ate from the forbidden tree, after which they were sent to Earth.</p>
    
    <div class="quran-verse">"And We said, 'O Adam, dwell, you and your wife, in Paradise and eat therefrom in [ease and] abundance from wherever you will. But do not approach this tree, lest you be among the wrongdoers.'" (Quran 2:35)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Humans have been honored by Allah with knowledge and responsibility.</li>
      <li>Shaytan is a clear enemy who uses deception to lead people astray.</li>
      <li>Repentance is always accepted by Allah when it is sincere.</li>
      <li>All tests in life are opportunities for spiritual growth.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Prophets</button>
</div>

<div class="story-page" id="idris">
  <h2>Prophet Idris (إدريس) - Enoch</h2>
  <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1580136579312-94651dfd596d?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80" alt="Ancient scroll" class="story-image">
  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Idris عليه السلام was a righteous man whom Allah raised to a high status. He is known for his wisdom and was the first to write with a pen. The Quran mentions that he was truthful and patient, and Allah elevated him to a high place.</p>
    
    <div class="quran-verse">"And mention in the Book, Idrees. Indeed, he was a man of truth and a prophet. And We raised him to a high station." (Quran 19:56-57)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Knowledge and wisdom are highly valued in Islam.</li>
      <li>Patience in fulfilling religious duties leads to elevated status.</li>
      <li>Truthfulness is a characteristic of all prophets.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Prophets</button>
</div>

<div class="story-page" id="nuh">
  <h2>Prophet Nuh (نوح) - Noah</h2>
  <img src="https://www.quranreading.com/pages/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/timthumb.jpg" alt="Stormy sea with ark" class="story-image">
  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Nuh عليه السلام preached to his people for 950 years, calling them to worship Allah alone. When they persistently rejected his message, Allah commanded him to build an ark. After the flood destroyed the disbelievers, Nuh and the believers were saved.</p>
    
    <div class="quran-verse">"And it was revealed to Nuh: 'None of your people will believe except those who have already believed. So do not be distressed by what they have been doing. And construct the ark under Our Eyes and with Our Inspiration.'" (Quran 11:36-37)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Patience and perseverance are essential in calling people to truth.</li>
      <li>Allah saves the believers from destruction.</li>
      <li>Disobedience to Allah leads to severe consequences.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Prophets</button>
</div>

<div class="story-page" id="hud">
  <h2>Prophet Hud (هود)</h2>
  <img src="https://myislam.sfo3.digitaloceanspaces.com/assets/2024/prophet-stories/hud/Asset-6%20Land.png" alt="Desert ruins" class="story-image">

  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Hud عليه السلام was sent to the people of 'Ad, who were known for their great strength and arrogance. He called them to worship Allah alone and abandon their idolatry. When they rejected him, Allah sent a destructive wind that destroyed them for seven days and nights.</p>
    
    <div class="quran-verse">"And to 'Ad [We sent] their brother Hud. He said, 'O my people, worship Allah; you have no deity other than Him. Will you not then fear Him?'" (Quran 7:65)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Arrogance and pride prevent people from accepting the truth.</li>
      <li>Physical strength is meaningless without spiritual guidance.</li>
      <li>Allah's punishment is severe for those who persistently reject His messengers.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Prophets</button>
</div>

<div class="story-page" id="salih">
  <h2>Prophet Salih (صالح)</h2>
  <img src="https://myislam.sfo3.digitaloceanspaces.com/assets/2024/prophet-stories/saleh/Footer.png" alt="Rock formation" class="story-image">
  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Salih عليه السلام was sent to the people of Thamud, who carved magnificent homes in mountains. He called them to worship Allah alone. As a sign, Allah brought forth a she-camel from a rock, but they killed it. Allah destroyed them with a mighty blast and earthquake.</p>
    
    <div class="quran-verse">"And to Thamud [We sent] their brother Salih. He said, 'O my people, worship Allah; you have no deity other than Him. There has come to you clear evidence from your Lord.'" (Quran 7:73)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Material prosperity without gratitude leads to destruction.</li>
      <li>Allah's signs should be appreciated and respected.</li>
      <li>Rejecting clear evidence of truth brings severe consequences.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Prophets</button>
</div>

<div class="story-page" id="ibrahim">
  <h2>Prophet Ibrahim (إبراهيم) - Abraham</h2>
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/69/95/f1/6995f165dfc416476b30bc589bc3e7d2.jpg" alt="Fire" class="story-image">
  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Ibrahim عليه السلام is known as the father of Prophets and the friend of Allah (Khalilullah). He rejected idol worship from a young age, destroyed the idols of his people, and was thrown into a huge fire as punishment. But Allah commanded the fire to be cool and safe for him. He also demonstrated ultimate submission to Allah by his willingness to sacrifice his son.</p>
    
    <div class="quran-verse">"They said, 'Burn him and support your gods - if you are to act.' We said, 'O fire, be coolness and safety upon Abraham.'" (Quran 21:68-69)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>True faith requires being ready to sacrifice everything for Allah.</li>
      <li>Allah protects His chosen servants in miraculous ways.</li>
      <li>Rejecting false gods requires courage and conviction.</li>
      <li>Complete trust in Allah leads to divine assistance.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Prophets</button>
</div>

<div class="story-page" id="lut">
  <h2>Prophet Lut (لوط) - Lot</h2>
  <img src="https://www.islamiclandmarks.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Wife-of-Prophet-Lut-a.s..jpg" alt="Destroyed city" class="story-image">
  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Lut عليه السلام was sent to the people of Sodom and Gomorrah, who engaged in immoral acts unknown before their time. He called them to righteousness and warned them of Allah's punishment. When they persisted in their sins and threatened to expel him, Allah destroyed their cities with a shower of stones.</p>
    
    <div class="quran-verse">"And [We sent] Lot, when he said to his people, 'Do you commit such immorality as no one has preceded you with from among the worlds? Indeed, you approach men with desire, instead of women. Rather, you are a transgressing people.'" (Quran 7:80-81)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Allah severely punishes societies that normalize immorality.</li>
      <li>Standing for truth often requires going against societal norms.</li>
      <li>Allah saves the believers even when entire nations are destroyed.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Prophets</button>
</div>

<div class="story-page" id="ismail">
  <h2>Prophet Ismail (إسماعيل) - Ishmael</h2>
  <img src="https://www.shutterstock.com/image-vector/allah-revealed-prophet-ibrahim-slaughter-260nw-2463379019.jpg" alt="Desert" class="story-image">
  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Ismail عليه السلام was the son of Ibrahim and Hajara. He was left with his mother in the valley of Mecca as a test from Allah. Together, they rebuilt the Kaaba and established the rites of Hajj. He is known for his patience and obedience to Allah, especially when Ibrahim was commanded to sacrifice him.</p>
    
    <div class="quran-verse">"And We gave him good tidings of Isaac, a prophet from among the righteous. And We blessed him and Isaac. But among their descendants are those who do good and those who clearly wrong themselves." (Quran 37:112-113)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Patience in difficult circumstances is greatly rewarded by Allah.</li>
      <li>Obedience to parents and Allah is a sign of true faith.</li>
      <li>The rites of Hajj commemorate the sacrifices of Ibrahim and Ismail.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Prophets</button>
</div>

<div class="story-page" id="ishaq">
  <h2>Prophet Ishaq (إسحاق) - Isaac</h2>
  <img src="https://w0.peakpx.com/wallpaper/811/48/HD-wallpaper-green-valley-in-beautiful-swiss-mountains-clouds-green-valley-mountains.jpg" alt="Green valley" class="story-image">
  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Ishaq عليه السلام was the second son of Ibrahim, born to Sarah in their old age as a miracle from Allah. He continued his father's mission of calling people to monotheism. His descendants included many prophets, including Yaqub, Yusuf, and eventually Isa.</p>
    
    <div class="quran-verse">"And We gave him [Abraham] Isaac(Ishaq) and Jacob(Yaqub) in addition, and all of them We made righteous." (Quran 21:72)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Allah's blessings come in unexpected ways and at unexpected times.</li>
      <li>Righteousness is passed down through generations when parents instill faith.</li>
      <li>The lineage of prophets continued through Ishaq, showing Allah's plan.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Prophets</button>
</div>

<div class="story-page" id="yaqub">
  <h2>Prophet Yaqub (يعقوب) - Jacob</h2>
  <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/18742774/pexels-photo-18742774/free-photo-of-big-tent-in-the-middle-of-a-desert.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=1" alt="Tent in desert" class="story-image">
  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Yaqub عليه السلام, also known as Israel, was the son of Ishaq and grandson of Ibrahim. He had twelve sons who became the progenitors of the twelve tribes of Israel. He endured great hardship when his son Yusuf was lost to him, showing remarkable patience and trust in Allah.</p>
    
   
        <div class="quran-verse">"And have patience (oh Muhammad) for Allah will not waste the reward of the righteous." (Quran 11:115)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Patience in the face of loss and hardship is a sign of strong faith.</li>
      <li>Family bonds are important but should not distract from worship of Allah.</li>
      <li>Allah's plan may involve temporary hardship for greater wisdom.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Prophets</button>
</div>

<div class="story-page" id="yusuf">
  <h2>Prophet Yusuf (يوسف) - Joseph</h2>
  <img src="https://al-islam.org/sites/default/files/part8e.gif" alt="Egyptian palace" class="story-image">
  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Yusuf عليه السلام had a remarkable life filled with trials and triumphs. As a boy, he was thrown into a well by his brothers, sold into slavery, and later imprisoned unjustly. Through his wisdom and trust in Allah, he rose to become a minister in Egypt. His story demonstrates how Allah rewards patience and righteousness.</p>
    
    <div class="quran-verse">"And Allah is predominant over His affair, but most of the people do not know." (Quran 12:21)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Hardship and trials are often followed by relief and success.</li>
      <li>Patience and trust in Allah are keys to overcoming difficulties.</li>
      <li>Forgiveness and reconciliation are noble qualities that bring peace.</li>
      <li>Allah's wisdom prevails even in seemingly tragic circumstances.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Prophets</button>
</div>

<div class="story-page" id="ayyub">
  <h2>Prophet Ayyub (أيوب) - Job</h2>
  <img src="https://www.aljumuah.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/The-Exemplary-Patience-of-Prophet-Ayy%C3%BBb-Job-AS-1.png" alt="Desert landscape" class="story-image">
  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Ayyub عليه السلام was known for his immense patience during severe trials. He lost his wealth, children, and health, yet remained steadfast in his worship of Allah. After years of suffering, he prayed to Allah, who restored his health and blessed him with even greater prosperity.</p>
    
    <div class="quran-verse">"And remember Our servant, Job, when he called to his Lord, 'Indeed, Satan has touched me with hardship and torment.'" (Quran 38:41)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>True faith is tested through hardship and suffering.</li>
      <li>Patience in adversity is greatly rewarded by Allah.</li>
      <li>Turning to Allah in times of distress brings relief and blessings.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Prophets</button>
</div>

<div class="story-page" id="shuayb">
  <h2>Prophet Shu'ayb (شعيب)</h2>
  <img src="https://destinationksa.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/71.jpg" alt="Marketplace" class="story-image">
  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Shu'ayb عليه السلام was sent to the people of Madyan, who were known for cheating in business and worshiping a tree called Al-Aykah. He called them to justice in their dealings and to worship Allah alone. When they rejected him, Allah destroyed them with a mighty earthquake.</p>
    
    <div class="quran-verse">"And to Madyan [We sent] their brother Shu'ayb. He said, 'O my people, worship Allah; you have no deity other than Him. And do not decrease from the measure and the scale.'" (Quran 11:84)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Justice in business transactions is a fundamental Islamic principle.</li>
      <li>Allah's punishment comes to those who cheat and oppress others.</li>
      <li>Worship of Allah requires honesty in all aspects of life.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Prophets</button>
</div>

<div class="story-page" id="musa">
  <h2>Prophet Musa (موسى) - Moses</h2>
  <img src="https://nooracademy.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Moses-in-Islam.webp" alt="Parted sea" class="story-image">
  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Musa عليه السلام was chosen by Allah to guide the Children of Israel and confront the tyranny of Pharaoh. His miracles included his staff turning into a serpent and his hand becoming shining white. He led his people out of Egypt after Allah parted the sea, drowning Pharaoh and his army.</p>
    
    <div class="quran-verse">"And We inspired to Moses, 'Strike with your staff the sea,' and it parted, and each portion was like a great towering mountain." (Quran 26:63)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Trust in Allah even when facing seemingly insurmountable challenges.</li>
      <li>Miracles happen only by Allah's permission to support His messengers.</li>
      <li>True leadership requires patience, courage, and reliance on Allah.</li>
      <li>Arrogance and tyranny are ultimately destroyed by divine justice.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Prophets</button>
</div>

<div class="story-page" id="harun">
  <h2>Prophet Harun (هارون) - Aaron</h2>
  <img src="https://www.islamiclandmarks.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Mount-Hor.jpg" alt="Mountain" class="story-image">
  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Harun عليه السلام was the older brother of Musa and was appointed by Allah to assist him in his mission to Pharaoh and the Children of Israel. He was eloquent in speech and helped Musa convey Allah's message. When Musa went to Mount Tur, Harun was left in charge, but the people began worshiping a golden calf.</p>
    
    <div class="quran-verse">"And We granted him his brother Harun as a prophet, after his request." (Quran 19:53)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Allah provides helpers and supporters for those who work in His cause.</li>
      <li>Leadership requires delegation and trust in others.</li>
      <li>Even prophets faced challenges with their communities.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Prophets</button>
</div>

<div class="story-page" id="dawud">
  <h2>Prophet Dawud (داود) - David</h2>
  <img src="https://central-asia.guide/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Harzati-daod-cave-entrance-1024x682.jpg" alt="Mountain fortress" class="story-image">
  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Dawud عليه السلام was given both prophethood and kingship. He was known for his beautiful recitation of the Zabur (Psalms) and his wisdom in judgment. Allah made iron pliable for him, and he was skilled in making armor. He defeated the mighty Goliath with a single stone.</p>
    
    <div class="quran-verse">"And We certainly gave David from Us bounty. [We said], 'O mountains, repeat [Our] praises with him, and the birds [as well].'" (Quran 34:10)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>True power comes from Allah, not physical strength.</li>
      <li>Combining spiritual authority with worldly responsibility requires wisdom.</li>
      <li>Allah blesses His servants with unique talents and abilities.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Prophets</button>
</div>

<div class="story-page" id="sulaiman">
  <h2>Prophet Sulaiman (سليمان) - Solomon</h2>
  <img src="https://nooracademy.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/WhatsApp-Image-2024-12-15-at-5.18.25-PM-2.jpeg" alt="Palace" class="story-image">
  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Sulaiman عليه السلام inherited prophethood and a great kingdom from his father Dawud. Allah granted him control over the wind, jinn, animals, and birds. He understood the language of birds and had a unique kingdom that no one after him would ever have.</p>
    
    <div class="quran-verse">"And to Solomon [We subjected] the wind - its morning [journey was that of] a month - and its afternoon [journey was that of] a month, and We made flow for him a spring of [liquid] copper." (Quran 34:12)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Allah's blessings should be used with gratitude and responsibility.</li>
      <li>True wisdom is understanding that all power comes from Allah.</li>
      <li>Justice and fairness are essential qualities of leadership.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Prophets</button>
</div>

<div class="story-page" id="ilyas">
  <h2>Prophet Ilyas (إلياس) - Elijah</h2>
  <img src="https://i.ytimg.com/vi/5JzHuKeLAvo/hq720.jpg?sqp=-oaymwEhCK4FEIIDSFryq4qpAxMIARUAAAAAGAElAADIQj0AgKJD&rs=AOn4CLBN5GeqpDwsU1eR94IwbVf39rMWsw" alt="Stormy sky" class="story-image">
  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Ilyas عليه السلام was sent to the people of Baalbek who worshiped an idol named Ba'al. He called them to worship Allah alone and warned them of punishment if they persisted in their disbelief. When they rejected him, Allah afflicted them with drought and famine.</p>
    
    <div class="quran-verse">"And indeed, Ilyas was from among the messengers. When he said to his people, 'Will you not fear Allah?'" (Quran 37:123-124)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Idol worship is a grave sin that leads to divine punishment.</li>
      <li>Prophets faced great opposition but remained steadfast.</li>
      <li>Allah's punishment often comes in forms that make people reflect.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Prophets</button>
</div>

<div class="story-page" id="alyasa">
  <h2>Prophet Alyasa (اليسع) - Elisha</h2>
  <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/44/Chester_Beatty_T_414_fol_90_r_Alyasa_choosing_his_successor.jpg/250px-Chester_Beatty_T_414_fol_90_r_Alyasa_choosing_his_successor.jpg" alt="Green field" class="story-image">
  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Alyasa عليه السلام was a successor to Prophet Ilyas and continued his mission. He was granted miracles by Allah, including healing the sick and even bringing the dead back to life. He called his people to monotheism during a time of widespread disbelief.</p>
    
    <div class="quran-verse">"And mention Ilyas in the Book. Indeed, he was surely truthful and a prophet. And We raised him to a high station. And among his descendants was Dawud and Sulaiman and Ayyub and Yusuf and Musa and Harun." (Quran 6:85-84)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Allah's work continues through successive generations of prophets.</li>
      <li>Miracles are granted by Allah to support His messengers.</li>
      <li>Continuity in conveying Allah's message is essential.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Prophets</button>
</div>

<div class="story-page" id="yunus">
  <h2>Prophet Yunus (يونس) - Jonah</h2>
  <img src="https://al-buraq.org/cdn/shop/articles/64DED6FD-0BAA-490D-B8D6-65661C1086E9.png?v=1628051995" alt="Whale in ocean" class="story-image">
  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Yunus عليه السلام was sent to the people of Nineveh. When they rejected him, he left in anger before receiving Allah's permission. He was swallowed by a large fish and remained in its belly for three days, repenting to Allah. After his supplication was accepted, he was cast ashore and returned to his people, who had then believed.</p>
    
    <div class="quran-verse">"And [mention] the man of the fish, when he went off in anger and thought that We would not decree [anything] upon him. And he called out within the darknesses, 'There is no deity except You; exalted are You. Indeed, I have been of the wrongdoers.'" (Quran 21:87)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Patience and perseverance are essential in conveying Allah's message.</li>
      <li>Sincere repentance is always accepted by Allah.</li>
      <li>Even prophets made mistakes and repented, showing humility.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Prophets</button>
</div>

<div class="story-page" id="zakariya">
  <h2>Prophet Zakariya (زكريا) - Zechariah</h2>
  <img src="https://myislam.sfo3.digitaloceanspaces.com/assets/2024/prophet-stories/zakariyah/Prophet%20Zakariyah%20Carpenter.png" alt="Mihrab" class="story-image">
  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Zakariya عليه السلام was the guardian of Maryam and a righteous priest in Jerusalem. He and his wife were elderly and childless, but he prayed to Allah for a righteous heir who would inherit his knowledge. Allah granted him a son, Yahya (John), despite their old age.</p>
    
    <div class="quran-verse">"[This is] a mention of the mercy of your Lord to His servant Zechariah, when he called to his Lord in a private supplication." (Quran 19:2-3)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Allah answers sincere prayers, even when they seem impossible.</li>
      <li>Righteousness and devotion to Allah are highly valued.</li>
      <li>Allah's blessings come in ways we might not expect.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Prophets</button>
</div>

<div class="story-page" id="yahya">
  <h2>Prophet Yahya (يحيى) - John</h2>
  <img src="https://www.isaandislam.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/yahya-2.jpg" alt="River" class="story-image">
  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Yahya عليه السلام was the son of Zakariya, born miraculously to elderly parents. He was given wisdom while still a child and lived a life of piety, humility, and devotion to Allah. He called people to repentance and prepared the way for Prophet Isa. He was martyred for his faith.</p>
    
    <div class="quran-verse">"[Allah said], 'O John, take the Scripture with determination.' And We gave him judgment [while yet] a child." (Quran 19:12)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Allah grants wisdom and piety even to the young.</li>
      <li>Standing for truth may require great sacrifice.</li>
      <li>Humility and devotion are qualities beloved to Allah.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
