<div class="story-page" id="isa">
  <h2>Prophet Isa (عيسى) - Jesus</h2>
  <img src="https://preview.redd.it/smo67caf07v61.jpg?width=640&crop=smart&auto=webp&s=4dad812f199d79441826dbd4b8416ea162742a2d" alt="Dove" class="story-image">
  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Isa عليه السلام was born miraculously to Maryam without a father. He was granted miracles by Allah, including healing the sick and raising the dead, all by Allah's permission. He called the Children of Israel to worship Allah alone and follow the Injil (Gospel). He was neither killed nor crucified but was raised to Allah.</p>
    
    <div class="quran-verse">"[And mention] when the angels said, 'O Mary, indeed Allah gives you good tidings of a word from Him, whose name will be the Messiah, Jesus, the son of Mary - distinguished in this world and the Hereafter and among those brought near [to Allah].'" (Quran 3:45)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Allah has power over all things, including creation without a father.</li>
      <li>Miracles happen only by Allah's permission and for His purpose.</li>
      <li>Isa was a human prophet and servant of Allah, not divine.</li>
      <li>Allah protects His chosen servants from harm.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Prophets</button>
</div>

<div class="story-page" id="muhammad">
  <h2>Prophet Muhammad (محمد) ﷺ</h2>
  <img src="https://www.middleeasteye.net/sites/default/files/styles/max_2600x2600/public/2023-06/Painting_Kaaba_1717_Uppsala%20University%20Library_Sweden.jpg.jpg?itok=_u2HaNCb" alt="Kaaba" class="story-image">
  <div class="story-content">
    <p>Prophet Muhammad ﷺ is the final messenger of Allah, sent as a mercy to all worlds. He received revelation over 23 years, which was compiled as the Quran. Despite facing persecution in Mecca, he patiently conveyed the message of Islam. After migrating to Medina, he established an Islamic society based on justice and compassion.</p>
    
    <div class="quran-verse">"And We have not sent you, [O Muhammad], except as a mercy to the worlds." (Quran 21:107)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="explanation">
    <h4>Lessons & Explanation</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Muhammad ﷺ is the perfect example for all humanity in character and conduct.</li>
      <li>Patience and perseverance in the face of adversity are essential qualities.</li>
      <li>Mercy and compassion should guide our interactions with all creation.</li>
      <li>The Quran is the final and complete guidance for humanity until the Day of Judgment.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <button class="back-btn" onclick="goBack()"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Prophets</button>
